hopobject.body: Do you need a work permit? prostate revive natural supplement Of the quartet representing the Bundesliga in Europe’s elite competition, Schalke look the least predictable. The 2-0 win against Leverkusen on Saturday corrected a leaky start to their season and they are pleased with the late-window signing of the maverick Kevin-Prince Boateng, for Â£9m from AC Milan. “This is the best league in the world and the best belong here,” said Boateng, whose career has wandered around enough, from Hertha Berlin to Spurs, Dortmund, Portsmouth and Serie  A, to make that sound like an informed conviction as much as polite praise.
